its \(y\)-intercept is \{ans_rule(5)\} and its \(x\)-intercept is \{ans_rule(5)\}.
$BR$BR
Here the curve \(x=y^2\) can be rewritten as a function of \(x\), \(g(x)=\) \{ans_rule(5)\}.

$BR$BR
The functions \(f(x)=x^2\) and \(g(x)=\) \{ans_rule(5)\} intersect when

\{
 BeginTable(center=>0).

  AlignedRow([
